modules.description: This module converts identifiers between Pascal, Camel, Snake, and Kebab case formats. It operates on string inputs representing variable or function names, transforming them to match different naming conventions used in code generation and parsing tasks. For example, it can convert "UserName" to "user_name" or "userName" as needed when translating between languages with different style conventions.

This module provides utilities for converting identifiers between common naming conventions like Pascal, Camel, Snake, and Kebab case. It operates on string inputs representing variable or function names, enabling seamless translation between languages with differing style conventions. For example, it can transform "UserName" into "user_name" or "userName" depending on the target language's requirements. These transformations are useful during code generation, parsing, and cross-language interoperability tasks.
